<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<jasperReport xmlns="http://jasperreports.sourceforge.net/jasperreports" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://jasperreports.sourceforge.net/jasperreports http://jasperreports.sourceforge.net/xsd/jasperreport.xsd" name="TermsAndConditions_Synergy" pageWidth="550" pageHeight="842" columnWidth="550" leftMargin="0" rightMargin="0" topMargin="0" bottomMargin="0" uuid="9c6a483f-6417-447b-bd8e-e58a3135df2d">
	<property name="ireport.zoom" value="1.0"/>
	<property name="ireport.x" value="0"/>
	<property name="ireport.y" value="0"/>
	<queryString>
		<![CDATA[SELECT 1 AS dummy]]>
	</queryString>
	<pageHeader>
		<band height="25" splitType="Stretch">
			<staticText>
				<reportElement stretchType="RelativeToBandHeight" x="0" y="0" width="550" height="25" uuid="2acf12aa-d5e2-4292-bbd9-3335e9a71df9"/>
				<box>
					<topPen lineWidth="0.5"/>
					<bottomPen lineWidth="0.5"/>
				</box>
				<textElement textAlignment="Center" verticalAlignment="Middle">
					<font fontName="Arial" size="14" isBold="true"/>
				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[Terms & Conditions of Trade]]></text>
			</staticText>
		</band>
	</pageHeader>
	<detail>
		<band height="727" splitType="Stretch">
			<textField isStretchWithOverflow="true">
				<reportElement stretchType="RelativeToBandHeight" x="0" y="0" width="550" height="727" isPrintWhenDetailOverflows="true" uuid="1f0092de-3de5-4aee-aa34-bbb71d5224e7"/>
				<textElement markup="styled">
					<font fontName="Arial" size="7"/>
				</textElement>
				<textFieldExpression><![CDATA["<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">1. Definitions</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.1.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Additional Fees</style> means any fee as may be charged by the Supplier in accordance with clause 7.3 of these Terms and Conditions.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.2.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Agreement</style> means this these Terms and Conditions and any Purchase Order, Credit Account Application, Guarantee and Indemnity, and schedules and annexures to it, as relevant and amended and substituted from time to time.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.3.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Bank Fee</style> means any charges incurred by the Client from their financial institution which includes but is not limited to: dishonour fees, interest, overdraft fees, foreign transaction fees.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.4.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Bank Account</style> means the Client's nominated bank account for Direct Debit payments.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.5.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Banking Day</style> means a day other than Saturday or Sunday, or a public holiday or bank holiday in New South Wales.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.6.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Card</style> means the Client's nominated credit or debit card for Direct Debit payments.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.7.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">CCA</style> means the Competition and Consumer Act 2010 (Cth), including the Australian Consumer Laws contained in schedule 2 of the CCA.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.8.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Client</style> means the person or entity specified on a Purchase Order or Credit Account Application (as relevant), or any person acting on behalf of and with the authority of the Client requesting the Supplier to provide the Goods or Services as specified in any proposal, quotation, order, invoice or other documentation.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.9.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Credit Account Application</style> means an application for credit with the Supplier.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.10.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Completion Date</style> means the last day of a hiring term specified under a Purchase Order, Credit Account Application or a request by the Client in writing (as relevant), or otherwise the date as agreed between the Client and the Supplier in writing or deemed to be agreed by the Client and the Supplier by operations of any terms and conditions.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.11.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Consultancy/Retainer Agreement or CA</style> means the Consultancy/Retainer Agreement entered into between the Supplier and Client.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.12.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Consequential Loss</style> mean all forms of indirect loss including loss of revenue, loss of profits, failure to recognise profits or savings and any other commercial and economic loss, howsoever caused.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.13.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Damage,</style> in relation to defects in Goods, means substantial structural damage only, such as breakage, but does not include any minor or cosmetic imperfections, such as chips or minor wear and tears.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.14.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Delivery of Goods or Delivery</style> has the meaning given in clause 8.1 of these Terms and Conditions.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.15.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Debit Day</style> means the day that payment by the Client is due.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.16.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Direct Debit</style> means the regular payment authorised by the Client for the Supplier to draw and collect payment from their Bank Account or Card on the Debit Day by provided the signed Authority to Charge a Credit Card to the Supplier in a similar form as annexed to these terms and conditions as Annexure \"A\", or otherwise provided or amended from time to time.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.17.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Driver Contract Agreement or DCA</style> means the Driver Contract Agreement entered into between the Supplier and the Client.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.18.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Force Majeure Event</style> means any event beyond a Party's reasonable control, including a/an fire, storm, flood, earthquake, explosion, accident, act of God, act of a public enemy, terrorist act, war, rebellion, insurrection, sabotage, epidemic, pandemic, quarantine restriction, government restriction, transportation embargo, power failure, failure of telecommunications network, malicious cyber-attacks, breakdown of plant or machinery, restrictions or delays affecting delivery of the Supplies, default of suppliers or subcontractors, shortage or unavailability of raw materials from normal sources of supply or the amendment or coming into force of any regulatory provision affecting the import or export of the Supplies or any ingredients or materials for production of the Supplies, and strike by third party employees other than a subcontractor or supplier of that Party, but in each case, provided always that the Party is without fault in causing the relevant event and the event, or its effects, could not have been prevented by reasonable precautions by that Party.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.19.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Guarantee and Indemnity</style> means each of guarantee and indemnity given by the Guarantor in the Personal/Directors Guarantee and Indemnity Form and in clause 22 of these Terms and Conditions.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.20.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Guaranteed Monies</style> has the meaning given in clause 22.2.1 of these terms and conditions.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.21.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Insurance</style> has the meaning given in clause 9.2.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.22.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Interest Rate</style> means the pre-judgment interest rate prescribed under Section 100 of the Civil Procedure Act 2005 (NSW) and Rule 36.7 of the Uniform Civil Procedure Rules 2005 (NSW), as published from time to time, and shall not exceed the maximum rate permissible by law.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.23.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Invoice Due Date</style> has the meaning given in clause 7.13.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.24.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Goods</style> means all Goods to be supplied by the Supplier (whether by sale and/or hire and/or any other service listed in this Agreement) to the Client pursuant to an Order made by the Client from time to time.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.25.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">GST</style> means Goods and Services Tax (GST) as defined within A New Tax System (Goods and Services Tax) Act 1999 (Cth).\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.26.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Guarantor</style> means each person(s) specified on the Personal/Director's Guarantee and Indemnity Form whom guarantees the performance of the Client's obligations under the Purchase Order or Credit Account Application (as relevant) and these terms and conditions.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.27.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Jobsite</style> means the Client's or any third parties jobsite(s) in which the Goods will be located from time to time.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.28.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Master Services Agreement or MSA</style> means the Master Services Agreement entered into between the supplier and the client.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.29.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Minimum Hire Period</style> means the period specified on the invoices, quotation, authority to hire, or any other forms as provided by the Supplier to the Client.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.30.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Order</style> means an order for the supply of Goods and/or Services made by the Client to the Supplier in accordance with clause 3 of these Terms and Conditions.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.31.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Order Variation Request</style> has the meaning given in clause 4.2 of these Terms and Conditions.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.32.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Personal/Directors Guarantee and Indemnity Form</style> means a document in a similar form annexed and marked \"A\" to these Terms and Conditions.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.33.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Price</style> means the Price payable (plus any GST) for the hire or purchase of Goods or provision of Services as agreed between the Supplier and the Client in accordance with clause 7 of these terms and conditions.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.34.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Price Variation Notice</style> has the meaning given in clause 7.5.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.35.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Price Variation Notice Period</style> means 10 days from the date the Price Variation Notice is served to the Client by the Supplier.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.36.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">PPSA</style> means the Personal Property Securities Act 2009 (Cth).\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.37.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Privacy Policy</style> means the Client's privacy policy which is available on their website.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.38.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Project</style> means each Client site at which Goods and/or Services are provided.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.39.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Purchase Order</style> means the document whereby the Client makes an Order pursuant to these Terms and Conditions.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.40.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Security</style> means in the form of cash, retention moneys, a security interest registration pursuant to the PPSA, an irrevocable and approved unconditional bank guarantee from a financial institution approved by the Supplier, or other form of security in the amount and form as determined by the Supplier from time to time.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.41.</style> Service means a notice or other communication given:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">1.41.1.</style> by email;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">1.41.2.</style> in person; or\n    <style isBold=\"true\">1.41.3.</style> by post,\npursuant to clause 23.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.42.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Services</style> means the services to be provided by the Supplier (whether in relation to sale and/or hire of Goods and/or any other service listed in this Agreement) to the Client pursuant to an Order made by the Client from time to time.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.43.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Supplier</style> means the person or entity stated on the purchase order providing the services.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.44.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Terms and Conditions</style> means these Terms and Conditions of trade and schedules and annexures to it, as amended and substituted from time to time.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.45.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Trust</style> means where the Client is part of an arrangement where the Client carries on its business on behalf of a trust or otherwise acts as a trustee, either express, implied or otherwise.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.46.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Variation Notice</style> has the meaning given in clause 2.18.1.\n<style isBold=\"true\">1.47.</style> <style isBold=\"true\">Variation Notice Period</style> means 30 days from the date the Variation Notice is served to the Client by the Supplier.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">2. Interpretation and Operations of Terms and Conditions</style>\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">General Operation</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.1.</style> Capitalised terms have the meanings specified in clause 1 of these Terms and Conditions.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.2.</style> To the extent that there is any conflict between these Terms and Conditions and a Purchase Order or Credit Account Application (as relevant), the provisions of these Terms and Conditions shall prevail, unless as expressly specified otherwise in the 'Special Conditions' section of the Purchase Order or Credit Account Application (as relevant).\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.3.</style> Specifying anything with the words \"including\" or similar expression does not limit what else is included unless express wording to the contrary.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.4.</style> The failure by either party to enforce any provision of these Terms and Conditions shall not be treated as a waiver of that provision, nor shall it affect that party's right to subsequently enforce that provision.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.5.</style> If any provision under these Terms and Conditions shall become invalid, void, illegal or deemed unenforceable under the laws, then:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.5.1.</style> that provision is severed from these Terms and Conditions to the extent necessary to remove the invalidity or illegality; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.5.2.</style> the validity, existence, legality and enforceability of the remaining provisions shall not be affected, prejudiced or impaired.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.6.</style> These Terms and Conditions and any contract to which they apply shall be governed by the laws of New South Wales and the parties irrevocably submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of the New South Wales.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.7.</style> Subject to clause 12 the Supplier shall be under no liability whatsoever to the Client for any indirect and/or Consequential Loss and/or expense (including loss of profit) suffered by the Client arising out of a breach by the Supplier of these Terms and Conditions (alternatively the Supplier's liability shall be limited to damages which under no circumstances shall exceed the Price of the Goods hired).\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.8.</style> The Supplier may reasonably licence and/or assign all or any part of its rights and/or obligations under this contract without the Client's consent.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.9.</style> The Client cannot licence or assign their rights and obligations without the written approval pursuant to clause 16.5.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.10.</style> The Supplier may elect to subcontract out of any part of the Services but shall not be relieved from any liability or obligation under this contract by so doing. Furthermore, the Client agrees and understands that they have no authority to give any instruction to any of the Supplier's sub-contractors without the authority of the Supplier.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.11.</style> Both parties warrant that they have the power to enter into this agreement and have obtained all necessary authorisations to allow them to do so, they are not insolvent and that this agreement creates binding and valid legal obligations on them.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.12.</style> Electronic signatures shall be deemed to be accepted by either party provided that the parties have complied with Section 9 of the Electronic Transactions Act 2000 (NSW), including any other applicable provisions of that Act or any Regulations referred to in that Act.\n\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Master Services Agreement (MSA) and/or Driver Contract Agreement (DCA) and/or Consultancy/Retainer Agreement (CA)</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.13.</style> Where the Client and the Supplier have entered into a Master Services Agreement (MSA) and/or a Driver Contract Agreement (DCA) and/or Consultancy/Retainer Agreement (CA), the terms and conditions of the MSA and/or DCA and/or CA take precedence over any other terms and conditions of trade included in this Purchase Order.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.14.</style> The Supplier acknowledges and warrants that any terms or definitions included in this Purchase Order do not apply to the services being performed with the exception of subclause 2.13 and 2.14\n\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Agreement</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.15.</style> The Client is taken to have accepted this Agreement and is immediately bound by these Terms and Conditions on the earlier of:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.15.1.</style> the Client placing an Order for the Goods and/or Services for the first time;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.15.2.</style> the Client accepting an invoice issued by the Supplier to the Client pursuant to clause 7.1 of these Terms and Conditions; or\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.15.3.</style> the Client accepting the Goods and/or Services.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.16.</style> The Client acknowledges these Terms and Conditions:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.16.1.</style> apply to any Order for the Goods and/or Services placed by the Client;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.16.2.</style> is taken to be incorporated into a Purchase Order or Credit Account Application (as relevant) and the Personal/Directors Guarantee and Indemnity Form; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.16.3.</style> govern the relationship between the Supplier and the Client in relation to an Order.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.17.</style> The Client agrees and acknowledges that:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.17.1.</style> they apply to the Supplier for a credit facility;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.17.2.</style> they have read and understood the Terms and Conditions and agrees to comply with these Terms and Conditions as amended from time to time;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.17.3.</style> if they enter into a Direct Debit arrangement, it is also bound by the Terms and Conditions of the direct debit service agreement;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.17.4.</style> the Supplier acting reasonably may withdraw further credit at any time without notice;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.17.5.</style> where it comprises more than one person or company, agrees that each such person and company is jointly and severally liable for all or any monies owing by the Client from time and time to the Supplier;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.17.6.</style> if the Client is a part of a Trust, the Trust shall be bound in their capacity as a trustee and is required to adhere to clause 21 of these Terms and Conditions;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.17.7.</style> it includes the Client's executors, administrators, successors and permitted assigns;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.17.8.</style> they agree the obligation to pay will be a continuing obligation notwithstanding any change in the constitution of the Client and all parties excluding the Supplier to this agreement are deemed to be the Client;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.17.9.</style> they warrant all information provided in the application form is complete, true and correct and acknowledges that the Supplier has relied on this information in considering whether to approve the application for credit; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">2.17.10.</style> they agree where the Supplier has extended credit, the Supplier may require the Client to provide Security. The Security provided under this Agreement is for due and proper performance of this Agreement by the Client. The Supplier may have recourse to the Security provided by the Client in respect of an amount due and payable, or which the Supplier reasonably believes is due and payable by the Client to the Supplier under or in connection with this Agreement which remains unpaid. The Supplier shall not be liable for any Loss occasioned by such recourse.\n\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Variation</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.18.1.</style> The Client agrees that the Supplier may, acting reasonably, amend these Terms and Conditions by notifying the Client in writing and providing amended terms and conditions. These changes shall be deemed to take effect from the date on which the Client accepts such changes, or otherwise at such time as the Client makes a further request for the Supplier to provide Goods to the Client.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.18.2.</style> Upon receipt of a Variation Notice, the Client may within the Variation Notice Period elect to terminate the Order, these Terms and Conditions, and any other agreement between the Supplier and the Client.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.18.3.</style> Where the Client exercises its right to terminate under clause 2.18.2, the Completion Date shall be varied to the date that is the end of the Variation Notice Period.\n<style isBold=\"true\">2.18.4.</style> The Client acknowledges and agrees that where it has received a Variation Notice from the Supplier and it has not elected to terminate an Order and these Terms and Conditions, the varied terms and conditions shall take effect on the date following the end of the Variation Notice Period.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">3. Orders</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">3.1.</style> The Client may place an Order from the Supplier pursuant to the following:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">3.1.1.</style> if the Client is a new Client placing an Order for the first time, by duly executing and delivering a Purchase Order or Credit Account Application (as relevant) to the Supplier; or\n    <style isBold=\"true\">3.1.2.</style> if the Client is an existing client placing subsequent Order(s), by submitting a request to the Supplier in writing.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">4. Errors and Omissions</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">4.1.</style> The Client acknowledges that:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">4.1.1.</style> the Client is responsible for the accuracy and completeness of any information submitted by the Client to the Supplier under an Order, including but not limited to information in relation to quantity, dimension, or any specification of Goods or scope of Services detailed in that Order; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">4.1.2.</style> except as a result of the Supplier's omission or gross negligence, the Supplier may hold the Client liable in respect of any loss, damage, liability, or cost suffered or incurred by the Supplier pursuant to any error or omission by the Client under an Order.\n<style isBold=\"true\">4.2.</style> Upon becoming aware of any error or omission under an Order, the Client must, as soon as practicable, submit a request to the Supplier for the variation of that Order in writing.\n<style isBold=\"true\">4.3.</style> On receipt of an Order Variation Request from the Client, the Supplier may, subject to its evaluation of the consequences of the requested variation, accommodate the request.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">5. Change in Control</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">5.1.</style> If the Client has placed an Order via a Credit Account Application, the Client must give the Supplier no less than fourteen (14) days prior written notice of any proposed change of ownership of the Client and/or any other change in the Client's details, including but not limited to changes in the Client's name, address, contact phone or fax number/s, change in trustees, or business practice.\n<style isBold=\"true\">5.2.</style> The Client shall be liable for any reasonable and direct loss, damage, liability or cost suffered or incurred by the Supplier as a result of the Client's failure to comply with clause 5.1, to the extent that such loss or cost is a reasonably foreseeable consequence of the non-compliance.\n<style isBold=\"true\">5.3.</style> The Supplier reserves the right to terminate this agreement upon providing 14 days' written notice if, in the Supplier's reasonable opinion, the change in control of the Client creates:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">5.3.1.</style> A conflict of interest;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">5.3.2.</style> A material risk to the Supplier's commercial or operational interests; or\n    <style isBold=\"true\">5.3.3.</style> Any other reasonably justified business concern that materially affects the Supplier's ability to continue the relationship.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">6. Brochures and Promotional Material</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">6.1.</style> The Client acknowledges and agrees that:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">6.1.1.</style> description and illustrations in the Supplier's brochures, promotional material and advertising are not to be taken as an exact representation of the articles described and are intended to present a general idea of the Goods;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">6.1.2.</style> all drawings, brochures and electronic information supplied are informative only; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">6.1.3.</style> all samples, illustrations, designs and specifications supplied to the Client by the Supplier remain the property of the Supplier and may not be copied, reverse engineered, disassembled, reproduced or used in part or whole without the prior written consent of the Supplier.\n<style isBold=\"true\">6.2.</style> To the extent permitted by law, the Supplier accepts no responsibility for the accuracy of illustrations, designs, samples, weights, dimensions, capacities and other particulars of the Goods, and will not be responsible for the cost of additional work, direct or consequential loss, liability, cost or damage pursuant to any variation in the Goods or otherwise than as depicted in brochures and promotional material.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">7. Price and Payment</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.1.</style> The Client agrees to pay the Price on any invoice issued by the Supplier to the Client in respect of an Order placed by the Client.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.2.</style> For the avoidance of doubt, the Price invoiced to the Client shall be determined on basis of the Supplier's quoted price as accepted by the Client when an Order is made by the Client (subject to clauses 7.3 to 7.8 of these Terms and Conditions) plus any Additional Fees and any such other costs charged pursuant to these Terms and Conditions (as relevant).\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.3.</style> The Supplier reserves the right to charge the following Additional Fees to the Client:\nFee: Administrative Fee - $100 + GST per week per Project for the hire duration.\nExample: 2 Projects x 4 weeks = $800 + GST total.\nTiming: Payable on first invoice; additional hire invoiced separately.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.4.</style> Any Additional Fees charged to the Client shall be applied to the Price as in accordance with this clause 7. The Client acknowledges such fees are reasonable, proportionate, and reflective of actual costs incurred.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.5.</style> Subject to clause 7.8, the Supplier reserves the right to amend its Price from time to time by giving 30 days written notice to the Client providing details of the amendments.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.6.</style> Upon receipt of a Price Variation Notice, the Client may within the Price Variation Notice Period elect to terminate any Order, these Terms and Conditions, and any other agreement between the Supplier and the Client.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.7.</style> Where the Client exercises its right to terminate under clause 7.6, the Completion Date shall be varied to the date that is the end of the Price Variation Notice Period.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.8.</style> The Client acknowledges and agrees that where it has received a Price Variation Notice from the Supplier and it has not elected to terminate an Order, the Supplier's new Price shall take effect in respect of any subsequent Order placed by the Client from the date of the Price Variation Notice.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.9.</style> Subject to prior notice given to the Client in writing, the Supplier reserves the right to change the Price:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.9.1.</style> if an Order Variation Request is made by the Client pursuant to clause 4.2 and is accepted by the Supplier; and/or\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.9.2.</style> in the event of any actual and demonstrable increase to the Supplier's operational costs and expenses, including labour, materials, or currency fluctuations.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.10.</style> Price variations pursuant to an accepted Order Variation Request will be charged in the same manner and detailed in writing on the Supplier's invoice.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.11.</style> The Client shall be responsible for all costs and expenses relevant to the provision of Goods and/or Services, including:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.11.1.</style> pickup and delivery of the Goods to and from the Supplier's depot;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.11.2.</style> if necessary, loading equipment and packaging costs;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.11.3.</style> any additional costs including taxes, fees, stamp duty, levy or charge imposed by government;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.11.4.</style> any extra costs due to the difference between information supplied by the Client and the actual site;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.11.5.</style> any excess or premium charged by any relevant insurance policy.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.12.</style> At the Supplier's sole discretion, and upon reasonable notice to the Client, a non-refundable deposit may be required.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.13.</style> Time for payment is of the essence. The invoice will be payable on the due date/s specified, which may be:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.13.1.</style> upon Delivery;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.13.2.</style> prior to Delivery;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.13.3.</style> by instalments/progress payments per the invoice schedule;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.13.4.</style> thirty (30) days following end of month in which invoice is issued;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.13.5.</style> the date specified on any invoice; or\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.13.6.</style> absent a date specification, seven (7) days following the invoice date.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.14.</style> Payment may be made by:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.14.1.</style> Cash;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.14.2.</style> cheque, bank cheque, or Card (surcharge may apply) in cleared funds; or\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.14.3.</style> any other method as agreed between the Client and the Supplier.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.15.</style> If a Client has elected to pay by Direct Debit, they acknowledge and agree that it is their responsibility to ensure:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.15.1.</style> the Bank Account and Card details provided are correct and up to date;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.15.2.</style> the Bank Account and Card can accept direct debit payment;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.15.3.</style> sufficient cleared funds are available on the Debit Day;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.15.4.</style> to notify the Supplier at least 5 business days from the Debit Day of any changes;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.15.5.</style> if their financial institution has stopped payment, to reactivate within 2 business days;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.15.6.</style> if Debit Day is not a Banking Day, the Supplier may debit on the following Banking Day; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">7.15.7.</style> to update details within 48 hours if notified of incorrect details or missed payment.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.16.</style> The Client shall not be entitled to set off against, or deduct from any outstanding invoice, any sums owed or claimed to be owed to the Client by the Supplier nor to withhold payment because part of that invoice is in dispute.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.17.</style> Unless otherwise stated the amount due does not include GST. The Client must pay GST on the amount due without deduction or set off on the Invoice Due Date.\n<style isBold=\"true\">7.18.</style> Time is of the essence with respect to all payment obligations, timeframes and deadlines pursuant to this Agreement.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">8. Delivery of Goods</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">8.1.</style> Delivery of the Goods is taken to occur at such time when:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">8.1.1.</style> the Client or the Client's nominated carrier takes possession of the Goods at the Supplier's premises; or\n    <style isBold=\"true\">8.1.2.</style> the Supplier (or the Supplier's nominated carrier) delivers the Goods to the Client's nominated address. Delivery is deemed to have occurred when the Goods arrive at the Client's nominated address even if the Client is not present.\n<style isBold=\"true\">8.2.</style> The cost of Delivery shall be borne by the Client in accordance with clause 7.11.\n<style isBold=\"true\">8.3.</style> The Supplier may deliver the Goods in separate stages. Each separate stage shall be invoiced and paid in accordance with these Terms and Conditions.\n<style isBold=\"true\">8.4.</style> Delivery must occur at such time agreed between the parties in writing.\n<style isBold=\"true\">8.5.</style> The Supplier will use reasonable endeavours to deliver the Goods on or before the estimated delivery date. The estimated delivery date is not a guarantee.\n<style isBold=\"true\">8.6.</style> The Supplier is not liable to the Client for any delay in meeting the estimated delivery date.\n<style isBold=\"true\">8.7.</style> In the event that the Client is unable to receive a Delivery at the agreed time, the Supplier shall be entitled to charge a reasonable fee for:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">8.7.1.</style> the actual costs incurred in relation to redelivery; and/or\n    <style isBold=\"true\">8.7.2.</style> the reasonable costs of storage, including warehousing fees.\n<style isBold=\"true\">8.8.</style> The Supplier is not liable for delay:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">8.8.1.</style> caused or contributed to by the Client;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">8.8.2.</style> caused or contributed by freight providers;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">8.8.3.</style> caused by the Client re-scheduling a build or installation date; or\n    <style isBold=\"true\">8.8.4.</style> caused by a Force Majeure Event or by an unforeseen circumstance outside of the reasonable control of the Company.\n<style isBold=\"true\">8.9.</style> On the occurrence of a Force Majeure Event, the Supplier shall not be deemed to be in breach or default and is entitled to delay, vary or cancel performance of any obligations.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">9. Title to the Goods and Insurances</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">9.1.</style> Where these Terms relate to hiring of Goods, the Client acknowledges and accepts that:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">9.1.1.</style> All title and ownership of the Goods are and will at all times remain with the Supplier;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">9.1.2.</style> To the extent that the Supplier owns any additions, replacements, attachments and improvements made to the Goods, the Supplier agrees to hire such items to the Client in accordance with these terms;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">9.1.3.</style> The Supplier shall be entitled to remove any addition, replacement, attachment and improvement made to the Goods;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">9.1.4.</style> the Client is fully responsible for the safekeeping of the Goods and shall indemnify the Supplier for all loss, damage or liability to the Goods, including theft; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">9.1.5.</style> the Client shall keep the Supplier indemnified against all losses arising under or in connection with the Client's use of the Goods during the hire period.\n<style isBold=\"true\">9.2.</style> Throughout the term during which the Goods are hired, the Client must take out and maintain from a reputable insurer:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">9.2.1.</style> insurance(s) covering loss or damage of Goods, including third party damage, fire, theft and burglary;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">9.2.2.</style> public liability insurance covering any loss, damage or injury to property;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">9.2.3.</style> any such other insurance covering any potential areas of liability; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">9.2.4.</style> any such other insurance as reasonably directed by the Supplier.\n<style isBold=\"true\">9.3.</style> Each Insurance must name the Supplier as insured parties and indemnify the Supplier in respect of the Client's hire and use of the Goods.\n<style isBold=\"true\">9.4.</style> The Client must provide to the Supplier upon request each certificate of currency of the Insurances.\n<style isBold=\"true\">9.5.</style> The Client agrees that it shall not use the Goods in such a manner as would cause an insurer to decline any Insurance claim.\n<style isBold=\"true\">9.6.</style> The Client agrees to return the Goods on the Completion Date.\n<style isBold=\"true\">9.7.</style> If the Client fails to return the Goods on the Completion Date, the Supplier or its agent may enter upon premises and take possession of the Goods.\n<style isBold=\"true\">9.8.</style> The Client is not authorised to pledge the Supplier's credit for repairs to the Goods or to create a lien over the Goods.\n<style isBold=\"true\">9.9.</style> Where these Terms relate to an agreement for the purchase of the Goods, clause 17 applies.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">10. PPSA</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">10.1.</style> In this clause financing statement, financing change statement, security agreement, and security interest has the meaning given to it by the PPSA.\n<style isBold=\"true\">10.2.</style> Upon assenting to these terms the Client acknowledges and agrees that these terms constitute a security agreement for the purposes of the PPSA and creates a security interest in:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">10.2.1.</style> all Goods presently in the Client's possession and after-acquired Goods supplied by the Supplier;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">10.2.2.</style> all present and after-acquired property of the Client pursuant to the charge granted under clause 11.1.\n    <style isBold=\"true\">10.2.3.</style> The Client undertakes to promptly sign any further documents required to register a financing statement or financing change statement.\n    <style isBold=\"true\">10.2.4.</style> indemnify, and upon demand reimburse, the Supplier for all reasonable expenses incurred in registering a financing statement;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">10.2.5.</style> not register a financing change statement without the prior written consent of the Supplier;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">10.2.6.</style> not register, or permit to be registered, a financing statement in favour of a third party without prior written consent;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">10.2.7.</style> immediately advise the Supplier of any material change in business practices.\n<style isBold=\"true\">10.3.</style> The Supplier and Client agree that sections 96, 115 and 125 of the PPSA do not apply to the security agreement.\n<style isBold=\"true\">10.4.</style> The Client waives their rights to receive notices under sections 95, 118, 121(4), 130, 132(3)(d) and 132(4) of the PPSA.\n<style isBold=\"true\">10.5.</style> The Client waives their rights as a grantor and/or a debtor under sections 142 and 143 of the PPSA.\n<style isBold=\"true\">10.6.</style> Unless otherwise agreed, the Client waives their right to receive a verification statement in accordance with section 157 of the PPSA.\n<style isBold=\"true\">10.7.</style> The Client must unconditionally ratify any actions taken by the Supplier under clauses 10.2.3 to 10.4.\n<style isBold=\"true\">10.8.</style> Subject to any express provisions to the contrary, nothing in these terms is intended to contract out of any provisions of the PPSA.\n<style isBold=\"true\">10.9.</style> Only to the extent that the hire exceeds a two (2) year period with right of renewal shall clause 10 apply as a PPS Lease in respect of Section 13 of the PPSA.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">11. Security and Charge</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">11.1.</style> To secure payment on the Goods supplied and any punctual payment of the Client's obligations, the Client charges all of its rights, title and interest in any land, real estate, personal property or other assets owned now or in the future, to secure performance of the Client's obligations under these terms.\n<style isBold=\"true\">11.2.</style> The Client indemnifies, and shall keep indemnified, the Supplier from and against all costs and disbursements that may arise pursuant to clause 11.1, including legal costs on an indemnity basis.\n<style isBold=\"true\">11.3.</style> However, the Client shall not be liable under clause 11.2 in the event of such costs arising by reason of the Supplier's gross negligence or wilful misconduct.\n<style isBold=\"true\">11.4.</style> The Client acknowledges the charge granted and expressly consents to any caveat or mortgage being lodged against any land or real property owned by the Client, provided that:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">11.4.1.</style> The Supplier has made a formal written demand for payment within seven (7) days and the Client has failed to comply; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">11.4.2.</style> The lodgment or registration is considered necessary by the Supplier to protect its interests.\n<style isBold=\"true\">11.5.</style> The Client irrevocably appoints the Supplier and each of its directors as the Client's attorney for the sole purpose of:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">11.5.1.</style> Executing any documents required to register or enforce the charge; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">11.5.2.</style> Lodging or withdrawing any caveat or mortgage to protect the Supplier's interests.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">12. Buyer Beware, Warranties Returns, and the CCA</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">12.1.</style> To the fullest extent permitted by law, the Client acknowledges that:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.1.1.</style> immediately upon Delivery, the Client is responsible for inspecting the Goods and to notify the Supplier immediately in writing of any Damage;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.1.2.</style> upon Delivery and absent notification, the Client is solely responsible for the quality, fitness for purpose and merchantability of the Goods; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.1.3.</style> the Client will not be entitled to a refund of any payment upon Delivery.\n<style isBold=\"true\">12.2.</style> To the fullest extent permitted by law, including the CCA:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.2.1.</style> upon Delivery and absent notification, the Goods are deemed accepted and free from any damage;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.2.2.</style> the Client assumes all risks in relation to the Goods upon Delivery; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.2.3.</style> unless otherwise contained expressly, the Supplier excludes all other representations, warranties, guarantees or terms in respect of the Goods.\n<style isBold=\"true\">12.3.</style> The Supplier acknowledges that:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.3.1.</style> the Client has statutory rights under the laws, including the CCA; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.3.2.</style> nothing in this document seeks to limit any right or remedy which cannot be limited.\n<style isBold=\"true\">12.4.</style> If the Client is a consumer within the meaning of the CCA, then:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.4.1.</style> the Supplier's liability for failure to comply with a 'Consumer Guarantee' is limited to the extent permitted by section 64A of Schedule 2 to replacement or repair of the Goods or re-supply of the Services or the cost thereof.\n<style isBold=\"true\">12.5.</style> If the Supplier is required to replace the Goods but is unable to do so, the Supplier may refund any money paid for the Goods.\n<style isBold=\"true\">12.6.</style> If the Client is not a consumer within the meaning of the CCA, the Supplier's liability for any defect or damage in the Goods is:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.6.1.</style> limited to the value of any express warranty provided;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.6.2.</style> limited to any warranty to which the Supplier is entitled, if the Supplier did not manufacture the Goods;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.6.3.</style> otherwise negated absolutely.\n<style isBold=\"true\">12.7.</style> Subject to this clause 12, returns will only be accepted provided that:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.7.1.</style> the Supplier has agreed that the Goods are defective or Damaged;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.7.2.</style> the Goods are returned immediately on inspection upon Delivery;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.7.3.</style> the Goods are returned at the Client's cost; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.7.4.</style> the Goods are returned in as close a condition to that in which they were delivered as is possible.\n<style isBold=\"true\">12.8.</style> Notwithstanding the above but subject to the CCA, the Supplier shall not be liable for any defect or Damage which may be caused or partly caused by:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.8.1.</style> the Client failing to properly maintain or store the Goods;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.8.2.</style> the Client using the Goods for any purpose other than that for which they were designed;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.8.3.</style> the Client continuing the use of the Goods after any defect became apparent;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.8.4.</style> the Client failing to follow any instructions or guidelines provided by the Supplier;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">12.8.5.</style> fair wear and tear, any accident, or act of God.\n<style isBold=\"true\">12.9.</style> However, the Supplier shall not exclude or limit its liability under clause 12.8 to the extent that any defect or Damage arises directly from the gross negligence or wilful misconduct of the Supplier.\n<style isBold=\"true\">12.10.</style> Notwithstanding anything contained in this clause if the Supplier is required by a law to accept a return then the Supplier will only accept a return on the conditions imposed by that law.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">13. Intellectual Property</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">13.1.</style> Where the Supplier has designed, drawn or developed Goods for the Client, the copyright in any designs and drawings and documents shall remain the property of the Supplier. Under no circumstances may such items be used without the express written approval of the Supplier.\n<style isBold=\"true\">13.2.</style> The Client warrants that all designs, specifications or instructions given to the Supplier will not cause the Supplier to infringe any patent, registered design or trademark and agrees to indemnify the Supplier against any action taken by a third party.\n<style isBold=\"true\">13.3.</style> The Client agrees that the Supplier may use for marketing purposes or entry into any competition, any documents, designs, drawings or Goods created for the Client.\n<style isBold=\"true\">13.4.</style> The Client acknowledges and agrees that any modifications, improvements, adaptations, feedback, or suggestions made by the Client in relation to the Goods, Services, or any intellectual property owned by the Supplier shall:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">13.4.1.</style> Automatically vest in and be assigned to the Supplier upon creation;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">13.4.2.</style> Be deemed the sole and exclusive property of the Supplier; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">13.4.3.</style> Where necessary, be formally transferred to the Supplier upon request.\n<style isBold=\"true\">13.5.</style> The Client waives any moral rights (to the extent permitted by law) in respect of any intellectual property created under Clause 13.4 and consents to the Supplier using, modifying, commercialising, or sublicensing such improvements without restriction.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">14. Default and Consequences of Default</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">14.1.</style> Interest on overdue invoices shall accrue daily from the date when payment becomes due until payment has been received in cleared funds, at the Interest Rate per annum.\n<style isBold=\"true\">14.2.</style> The Client acknowledges and agrees that:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">14.2.1.</style> the interest charged is a genuine pre-estimate of the loss likely to be suffered by the Supplier due to delay in receiving payment;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">14.2.2.</style> such loss includes administrative costs, financing costs, and opportunity costs; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">14.2.3.</style> the application of interest is not a penalty but a reasonable remedy for late payment.\n<style isBold=\"true\">14.3.</style> If the Client owes the Supplier any money the Client shall indemnify the Supplier from all costs and disbursements reasonably incurred in recovering the debt.\n<style isBold=\"true\">14.4.</style> However, the Client shall not be required to indemnify the Supplier pursuant to clause 14.3 to the extent that costs arise directly from the Supplier's gross negligence, wilful misconduct, or wrongful act.\n<style isBold=\"true\">14.5.</style> If the Client does not pay by the due date, the Supplier may issue a written demand requiring payment within seven (7) days. The Client must pay, in addition to the invoice sum, any legal costs incurred.\n<style isBold=\"true\">14.6.</style> If a Client's payment transaction is subsequently reversed, the Client shall be liable for the reversed amount plus any further costs incurred where such reversal is found to be illegal, fraudulent or in contravention of the Client's obligations.\n<style isBold=\"true\">14.7.</style> The Supplier shall be entitled to cancel all or any part of any order which remains unfulfilled and all amounts owing shall become immediately payable if:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">14.7.1.</style> any money payable to the Supplier becomes overdue, or will be unable to be paid when due;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">14.7.2.</style> the Client has exceeded any applicable credit limit;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">14.7.3.</style> the Client becomes insolvent or enters into an arrangement with creditors; or\n    <style isBold=\"true\">14.7.4.</style> a receiver, manager, liquidator or similar person is appointed in respect of the Client.\n<style isBold=\"true\">14.8.</style> The Client acknowledges that clauses 14.7.1 to 14.7.4 are essential terms and any breach shall entitle the Supplier to:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">14.8.1.</style> Enforce its rights under clause 14.7, including demanding immediate payment;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">14.8.2.</style> Suspend or cancel any unfulfilled orders; and/or\n    <style isBold=\"true\">14.8.3.</style> Terminate this Agreement and any other agreements with the Client by providing written notice.\n<style isBold=\"true\">14.9.</style> Where the Supplier terminates under clause 14.8, the Supplier shall not be liable for any loss, liability, damages, costs or expenses of the Client arising out of or in connection with the termination.\n<style isBold=\"true\">14.10.</style> At any time after a default has occurred, the Supplier may immediately and without notice undertake any form of enforcement action available to it by law.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">15. Cancellation</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">15.1.</style> Without prejudice to any other remedies, if at any time the Client is in breach of any obligation the Supplier may suspend or terminate the supply of Goods to the Client. The Supplier will not be liable to the Client for any loss or damage as a result of such suspension or termination, except to the extent that such exclusion is not permitted under applicable law.\n<style isBold=\"true\">15.2.</style> The Supplier may cancel any contract or cancel delivery of Goods at any time before the Goods are delivered by giving written notice. On giving such notice the Supplier shall repay to the Client any money paid for the Goods. The Supplier shall not be liable for any loss or damage arising from such cancellation.\n<style isBold=\"true\">15.3.</style> In the event that the Client cancels delivery of Goods the Client shall be liable for any direct loss incurred by the Supplier including but not limited to any loss of profits and any cost of materials, labour and other costs incurred.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">16. Hire of Goods</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">16.1.</style> Hire charges shall commence from the time the Goods leave the Supplier's premises and shall continue until the Goods are returned, and/or until the expiry of the Minimum Hire Period, whichever last occurs.\n<style isBold=\"true\">16.2.</style> The Completion Date or the date upon which the Client advises of termination shall in all cases be treated as a full day's hire.\n<style isBold=\"true\">16.3.</style> No allowance can be made for time during which the Goods are not in use unless the Supplier confirms special prior arrangements in writing. In the event of Goods breakdown, hiring charges will not be payable during the time the Goods are not working, unless the condition is due to negligence or misuse by the Client.\n<style isBold=\"true\">16.4.</style> The Client shall:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.1.</style> maintain the Goods as is required by the Supplier;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.2.</style> notify the Supplier immediately by telephone of any mechanical breakdown or accident;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.3.</style> be responsible to satisfy itself at commencement of the hire that the Goods are suitable for its purposes;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.4.</style> operate the Goods safely, strictly in accordance with the law, only for its intended use;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.5.</style> ensure that all persons operating the Goods are suitably instructed and hold a current Certificate of Competency and/or are fully licensed;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.6.</style> comply with all occupational health and safety laws;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.7.</style> on termination of the hire, deliver the Goods complete with all parts and accessories, clean and in good order;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.8.</style> keep the Goods in their own possession and control and shall not be entitled to lien over the Goods;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.9.</style> not on hire, sublicence or lease the Goods to a third party without written consent from the Supplier;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.10.</style> Provide a list of the Jobsites where the Client anticipates the Goods will be located;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.11.</style> not alter or make any additions to the Goods or interfere with any identifying marks;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.12.</style> employ the Goods solely in its own work;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.13.</style> not exceed the recommended or legal load and capacity limits;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.14.</style> not use or carry any illegal, prohibited or dangerous substance; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.4.15.</style> not fix any of the Goods as to make them legally a fixture forming part of any freehold.\n<style isBold=\"true\">16.5.</style> If written consent is given from the Supplier in clause 16.4.9, and the Client on hires, sublicences or leases the Goods to a third party, the Client acknowledges they:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.5.1.</style> remain liable for the Goods;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.5.2.</style> are required to maintain insurance of those Goods;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.5.3.</style> will advise the Supplier the location as to where the Goods will be kept;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.5.4.</style> will maintain a record of the list of third parties and Jobsites;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.5.5.</style> will provide written notice within 24 hours if the third party goes into liquidation; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.5.6.</style> shall ensure any agreement with the third-party expressly acknowledges the Supplier's ownership.\n<style isBold=\"true\">16.6.</style> The Client must ensure the Goods are not dismantled by any party other than the Supplier.\n<style isBold=\"true\">16.7.</style> The Client will be required to pay the Supplier's reasonable costs to recover any costs incurred as a result of the Client's breach of clauses 16.5 and 16.6.\n<style isBold=\"true\">16.8.</style> Immediately on request by the Supplier, the Client will pay:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.8.1.</style> the new list price of any Goods that are destroyed, written off or not returned;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.8.2.</style> all costs incurred in cleaning the Goods;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.8.3.</style> all costs of repairing any damage caused by ordinary use up to ten percent (10%) of the new list price;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.8.4.</style> the cost of repairing any damage caused by the negligence of the Client;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.8.5.</style> the cost of repairing any damage caused by vandalism or other than by ordinary use; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">16.8.6.</style> any lost hire fees the Supplier would have otherwise been entitled to.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">17. Sale of Goods</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">17.1.</style> Risk of damage to or loss of the Goods passes to the Client on Delivery and the Client must insure the Goods on or before Delivery.\n<style isBold=\"true\">17.2.</style> If any of the Goods are damaged or destroyed following delivery but prior to ownership passing to the Client, the Supplier is entitled to receive all insurance proceeds payable for the Goods.\n<style isBold=\"true\">17.3.</style> If the Client requests the Supplier to leave Goods outside the Supplier's premises for collection or to deliver the Goods to an unattended location then such Goods shall be left at the Client's sole risk.\n<style isBold=\"true\">17.4.</style> In the case of second hand Goods, unless the Client is a consumer under the CCA, the Client acknowledges that it has had full opportunity to inspect the second hand Goods prior to delivery and accepts them with all faults and that any implied warranty is expressly excluded.\n<style isBold=\"true\">17.5.</style> Cancellation will not be permitted for Goods made to the Client's specifications, or for non-stock list items.\n<style isBold=\"true\">17.6.</style> The Supplier and the Client agree that title and ownership of the Goods shall not pass until:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">17.6.1.</style> the Client has paid the Supplier all amounts owing; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">17.6.2.</style> the Client has met all of its other obligations to the Supplier.\n<style isBold=\"true\">17.7.</style> Receipt by the Supplier of any form of payment other than cash shall not be deemed to be payment until that form of payment has been honoured, cleared or recognised.\n<style isBold=\"true\">17.8.</style> The Client further acknowledges and agrees that:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">17.8.1.</style> until ownership of the Goods passes, the Client is only a bailee of the Goods;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">17.8.2.</style> the Client must not sell, dispose, or otherwise part with possession of the Goods other than in the ordinary course of business;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">17.8.3.</style> the Client shall not convert or process the Goods or intermix them with other goods;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">17.8.4.</style> The Client irrevocably authorises the Supplier to enter any premises where the Goods are kept and recover possession of the Goods;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">17.8.5.</style> the Supplier may recover possession of any Goods in transit whether or not Delivery has occurred;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">17.8.6.</style> the Client shall not charge or grant an encumbrance over the Goods while they remain the property of the Supplier; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">17.8.7.</style> the Supplier may commence proceedings to recover the Price notwithstanding that ownership has not passed.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">18. Manufacturing and Supply Services</style>\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Scope of Services</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">18.1.</style> The Supplier shall manufacture and supply the products, components, or fabricated structures (\"Goods\") as described in any accepted quotation, Purchase Order, or written request from the Client.\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Client's Obligations and Responsibility for Information</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">18.2.</style> The Client shall provide all specifications, architectural plans, structural drawings, dimensions, load requirements, finishes, and any other necessary documentation at the time of placing the order.\n<style isBold=\"true\">18.3.</style> The Supplier shall have no obligation to verify the accuracy of the Client's information, and shall not be liable for any loss, delay, defect, or additional cost arising from incomplete, ambiguous, or incorrect instructions.\n<style isBold=\"true\">18.4.</style> If the Client requests amendments to the Goods after manufacturing has commenced, the Supplier may suspend performance and issue a revised quote.\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Design and Drawing Interface</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">18.5.</style> Where manufacturing relies on the Supplier's design input, the Supplier shall provide draft drawings for the Client's review. The Client must respond within five (5) business days with approval or reasonable amendment requests. Failure to respond shall be deemed acceptance.\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Delivery and Risk</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">18.6.</style> Delivery of Goods shall be deemed complete when the Goods are collected by the Client or delivered to the address nominated by the Client. All risk in the Goods passes to the Client upon delivery.\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Standards and Disclaimer</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">18.7.</style> The Supplier shall manufacture in accordance with relevant Australian Standards. However, unless explicitly agreed in writing, the Supplier gives no warranty that the Goods are fit for any particular purpose, and the Client is solely responsible for ensuring the Goods are suitable for their intended use.\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Limitation of Liability</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">18.8.</style> To the fullest extent permitted by law:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">18.8.1.</style> the Supplier shall not be liable for any Consequential Loss or delay;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">18.8.2.</style> the Supplier's liability in respect of any defective Goods shall be limited to the repair, replacement, or refund of the affected Goods only; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">18.8.3.</style> the Client acknowledges that no representation or warranty has been made that the Goods will be suitable for the Client's purpose.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">19. Design and Detailing Services</style>\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Scope of Services</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">19.1.</style> The Supplier shall provide scaffold or structural design services, which may include preparation of draft and final drawings, general notes, computations, and formal design certification.\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Engagement and Variations</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">19.2.</style> The Supplier's obligation to perform design services arises only upon formal acceptance of its quotation. Any changes to the scope must be agreed in writing, and the Supplier shall be entitled to charge additional fees for variations outside the original scope.\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Approval Process</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">19.3.</style> The Supplier shall issue draft designs for the Client's review. The Client must respond within five (5) business days. Failure to respond shall be deemed acceptance.\n<style isBold=\"true\">19.4.</style> The Supplier may rely on the Client's approval as full confirmation that the design meets all required site-specific, regulatory, and functional needs.\n<style isBold=\"true\">19.5.</style> The Supplier shall not be responsible for errors, omissions, or conflicts arising due to unapproved modifications, incorrect client input, or the actions of third parties.\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Final Deliverables and Completion</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">19.6.</style> Upon Client approval of the draft, the Supplier shall issue final drawings, general notes, and (where applicable) a formal design certificate. Issuance of these documents constitutes full performance and completion of the Supplier's design service obligations.\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Use and Reliance on Design</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">19.7.</style> The Client acknowledges that the Supplier's design is based solely on information provided by the Client. The Supplier shall not be liable for any use or reliance on the design where the Client fails to provide accurate, up-to-date, or complete information.\n<style isBold=\"true\">19.8.</style> The detailing and shop drawings may be reviewed by other parties, but the Supplier accepts no liability for the outcomes of such reviews.\n<style isBold=\"true\">19.9.</style> The Client is solely responsible for ensuring that the design is reviewed and approved by all relevant authorities and incorporated correctly into the final construction or installation.\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Intellectual Property and Restrictions on Use</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">19.10.</style> All intellectual property in the design, drawings, notes, computations, certificates, and other deliverables created by the Supplier remains the sole and exclusive property of the Supplier. The Client shall not copy, modify, reproduce, share, or use any of the Supplier's documents for any project other than that for which they were issued, without the Supplier's prior written consent.\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Exclusion of Liability</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">19.11.</style> To the fullest extent permitted by law, the Supplier shall not be liable for:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">19.11.1.</style> any direct or indirect loss suffered by the Client or third parties arising from misuse or incorrect implementation of the design;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">19.11.2.</style> any cost, delay, rework, or damage incurred due to misinterpretation, misapplication, or alteration of the Supplier's design by others; or\n    <style isBold=\"true\">19.11.3.</style> any regulatory, site-specific, or engineering approvals not obtained by the Client.\nThe Supplier's total liability in connection with the design services shall not exceed the amount of the fees paid for those services.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">20. Testing</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">20.1.</style> Testing shall be conducted at the Certified Testing Body's discretion using methods determined by the Australian Standards. All costs, fees, and charges associated with testing shall be borne solely by the Client.\n<style isBold=\"true\">20.2.</style> The Client shall provide written notice of any specific testing requirements prior to order placement. The Testing Body shall be entitled to rely on the accuracy of such information.\n<style isBold=\"true\">20.3.</style> Attendance by the Client at any agreed testing shall be at the Client's cost and subject to reasonable prior notice.\n<style isBold=\"true\">20.4.</style> In the event that the Goods fail to meet agreed testing criteria due solely to a manufacturing defect, the Testing Body shall have no liability for any re-testing, rework, delay, or cost unless caused solely by its proven negligence.\n<style isBold=\"true\">20.5.</style> The Testing Body shall not be liable for any failure to meet testing outcomes where such failure arises from reliance on inaccurate, ambiguous, or incomplete information provided by the Client.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">21. Privacy</style>\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Privacy Act Authority</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">21.1.</style> The privacy of your personal information is important to the Supplier, and we will ensure that it is held, used and disclosed in accordance with the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) and the Supplier's Privacy Policy.\n<style isBold=\"true\">21.2.</style> The Supplier's Privacy Policy forms part of these Terms and Conditions and is incorporated by reference.\n<style isBold=\"true\">21.3.</style> The following is an outline of certain matters relating to the collection and use of your personal information in connection with this application for credit.\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Collecting your personal information</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">21.4.</style> The Supplier collects personal information to assess this application for credit and to provide the Goods and/or Services requested.\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Using and disclosing personal information</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">21.5.</style> By submitting the credit application, the Client consents to the Supplier:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">21.5.1.</style> Giving a credit reporting agency certain personal information including identifying details, payment history, and credit applications;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">21.5.2.</style> Seeking from or giving the Client information or opinions about the Client's credit worthiness from trade referees, creditors, bankers, or credit reporting agencies;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">21.5.3.</style> Using and disclosing Client's personal information to help provide or tell the Client about products or services, for internal administration, and for market research;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">21.5.4.</style> Giving to a guarantor information about the Client's creditworthiness relating to the guarantee; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">21.5.5.</style> Disclosing the Client's personal information to government bodies or the Supplier's agents, contractors and advisers.\n<style size=\"8\" isBold=\"true\" isItalic=\"true\">Accessing your personal information</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">21.6.</style> The Client can request access/corrections to the personal information held by the Supplier at any time unless the Supplier is prevented by law from doing so.\n<style isBold=\"true\">21.7.</style> The Supplier will destroy personal information upon the Client's written request unless it is required to fulfil the obligations of this Agreement or by law.\n<style isBold=\"true\">21.8.</style> The Client can make a privacy complaint in writing via e-mail. The Supplier will respond within seven (7) days and make a decision within thirty (30) days.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">22. Unpaid Seller's Rights</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">22.1.</style> Where the Client has left any item with the Supplier for repair, modification, exchange or other service and the Supplier has not received the whole of any monies owing, the Supplier shall have:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">22.1.1.</style> a lien on the item; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">22.1.2.</style> the right to retain or sell the item, such sale to be undertaken in accordance with applicable legislation.\n<style isBold=\"true\">22.2.</style> The lien of the Supplier shall continue despite the commencement of proceedings or judgment for any monies owing having been obtained against the Client.\n<style isBold=\"true\">22.3.</style> The Client is obligated to inform the Supplier of the location of any material the subject of this Agreement within 24 hours of any written request and failure to do so is a breach of an essential term.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">23. Building and Construction Industry Security of Payments Act 1999</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">23.1.</style> At the Supplier's sole discretion, if there are any disputes or claims for unpaid Goods then the provisions of the Building and Construction Industry Security of Payments Act 1999 may apply.\n<style isBold=\"true\">23.2.</style> Nothing in this agreement is intended to have the effect of contracting out of any applicable provisions of the Building and Construction Industry Security of Payments Act 1999 of New South Wales, except to the extent permitted by the Act where applicable.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">24. Trusts</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">24.1.</style> If the Client at any time is acting in the capacity of trustee of any Trust then, whether or not the Supplier has awareness of the Trust, the Client covenants with the Supplier as follows:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">24.1.1.</style> the Agreement extends to all rights of indemnity which the Client now or subsequently may have against the Trust and the trust fund;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">24.1.2.</style> the Client has full and complete power and authority under the Trust to enter into this Agreement and will not release the right of indemnity or commit any breach of trust;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">24.1.3.</style> The Client will not without consent in writing of the Supplier (not to be unreasonably withheld), cause, permit, or suffer any of the following events:\n        <style isBold=\"true\">(a)</style> the removal, replacement or retirement of the Client as trustee;\n        <style isBold=\"true\">(b)</style> any alteration to or variation of the terms of the Trust;\n        <style isBold=\"true\">(c)</style> any advancement or distribution of capital of the Trust; or\n        <style isBold=\"true\">(d)</style> any resettlement of the trust property.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">25. Guarantee and Indemnity</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">25.1.</style> In consideration of the Supplier agreeing to supply Goods and/or Services to the Client, each Guarantor agrees to be bound by the obligations and responsibilities as set out in the Personal/Directors Guarantee and Indemnity Form.\n<style isBold=\"true\">25.2.</style> Each Guarantor:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">25.2.1.</style> unconditionally and irrevocably guarantees the performance of the Client's obligations under these terms including payment of any amount owing (\"Guaranteed Monies\"); and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">25.2.2.</style> covenants to pay the Supplier on demand any amount owing by the Client.\n<style isBold=\"true\">25.3.</style> Where the Personal/Directors Guarantee and Indemnity Form is signed by more than one (1) Guarantor, each Guarantor acknowledges that it shall be held jointly and severally liable with all other Guarantors for the Guaranteed Monies.\n<style isBold=\"true\">25.4.</style> Each Guarantor indemnifies the Supplier against any reasonable and direct losses, liabilities, damages, costs or expenses suffered or incurred out of or in connection with:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">25.4.1.</style> the exercise of any powers, rights or remedies as a result of any direct breach by the Client or the Guarantor;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">25.4.2.</style> enforcing the Supplier's rights as a result of material breach;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">25.4.3.</style> the Client's failure to perform, or unreasonable delay in performing, any of the Client's obligations; or\n    <style isBold=\"true\">25.4.4.</style> under these terms, a Purchase Order or Credit Account Application Form, the Personal/Directors Guarantee and Indemnity Form and/or relevant laws.\n<style isBold=\"true\">25.5.</style> To secure payment of all monies payable under this Guarantee and Indemnity, the Guarantor charges its interest in real property and personal property, held now or acquired in the future.\n<style isBold=\"true\">25.6.</style> If the Guarantor defaults on their obligations, the Guarantor agrees to execute a mortgage or other instrument of security, or to consent to the registration of a caveat.\n<style isBold=\"true\">25.7.</style> If the Guarantor fails to execute the requested documents within a reasonable time (not less than 7 days), the Guarantor appoints the Supplier or its nominee as their lawful attorney for the sole purpose of executing such documents.\n<style isBold=\"true\">25.8.</style> The Supplier may lodge a caveat to protect its interests. The Guarantor consents to lodgement of such a caveat but reserves the right to dispute any caveat lodged in bad faith.\n<style isBold=\"true\">25.9.</style> The Guarantor waives all rights inconsistent with this clause, to the extent permissible under applicable law. This clause does not limit the Guarantor's rights under the Australian Consumer Law.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">26. Notice</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">26.1.</style> Unless stated otherwise, any notice, consent, or communication under these terms must:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">26.1.1.</style> be in writing, in English, and signed by or on behalf of the sender;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">26.1.2.</style> be addressed to the recipient at its designated address or email; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">26.1.3.</style> be delivered by hand, pre-paid mail (airmail if international), or email.\n<style isBold=\"true\">26.2.</style> A notice is deemed received:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">26.2.1.</style> if hand-delivered, upon delivery;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">26.2.2.</style> if posted, on the 3rd business day (or 7th business day if international) after posting;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">26.2.3.</style> if emailed, when the sender receives an automated delivery confirmation or 5 hours after sending (unless a delivery failure message is received), whichever occurs first.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">27. Dispute Resolution</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">27.1.</style> The dispute resolution process under this clause does not apply to debt recovery and the enforcement of unpaid monies.\n<style isBold=\"true\">27.2.</style> Nothing in this clause prevents a Party from applying for an urgent injunctive, declaratory, or other interlocutory or equitable relief before an appropriate court.\n<style isBold=\"true\">27.3.</style> If any Party believes that there is a Dispute, that Party must notify the other Party in writing, specifying the nature and substance of the Dispute (Dispute Notice).\n<style isBold=\"true\">27.4.</style> Upon an issue of a Dispute Notice, the Parties must respectively appoint a senior representative to resolve the Dispute by good faith negotiations within 7 days.\n<style isBold=\"true\">27.5.</style> The Parties agree that the obligations of the Parties in the Contract continue notwithstanding the existence of any Dispute.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">28. Modern Slavery Compliance</style>\n<style isBold=\"true\">28.1.</style> This clause applies only if the Customer notifies the Supplier that it requires compliance with Modern Slavery obligations. If not required, this clause shall be deemed of no effect.\n<style isBold=\"true\">28.2.</style> For the purpose of this clause, Modern Slavery has the same meaning given to it in the Modern Slavery Act 2018 (Cth).\n<style isBold=\"true\">28.3.</style> The Supplier agrees to be bound by and comply with the terms set out in the addendum to these terms and conditions and otherwise:\n    <style isBold=\"true\">28.3.1.</style> take reasonable steps to ensure that Modern Slavery is not present within its operations or supply chain;\n    <style isBold=\"true\">28.3.2.</style> cooperate with any reasonable due diligence or reporting requests from the Customer regarding Modern Slavery risks; and\n    <style isBold=\"true\">28.3.3.</style> notify the Customer if it becomes aware of any actual or suspected Modern Slavery practices within its supply chain.\n\n<style size=\"9\" isBold=\"true\">Addendum - Modern Slavery Commitment</style>\n\nHuman rights abuses are not permitted in any form in our supply chain. Suppliers must not commit or be involved in the committing of any human rights abuses, including forced or involuntary labour, human trafficking, discrimination, sexual exploitation or other exploitative practices. Suppliers must ensure they do not employ, directly or indirectly, workers under the local legal age of employment. If the local legislation is silent on the minimum age for employment, 15 years old is the minimum age for the purpose of this Code. Workers under the age of 18 shall only perform work in accordance with legal requirements such as working hours, wages and working conditions and subject to any requirement requiring education and training.\n\nSupplier must maintain and enforce policies and procedures designed to prevent modern slavery in its business and supply chain.\n\nThe Supplier must, upon reasonable request, provide the Customer with information regarding its supply chain practices, including evidence of compliance with modern slavery laws."]]></textFieldExpression>
			</textField>
		</band>
	</detail>
</jasperReport>
